Package edu.lehigh.cse216.rdm325.backend

Class DataRowComment

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.lehigh.cse216.rdm325.backend.DataRowComment
  • public class DataRowComment
extends java.lang.Object
    DataRow holds a row of information. A row of information consists of an identifier, strings for a "subject" and "message", and a creation date. Because we will ultimately be converting instances of this object into JSON directly, we need to make the fields public. That being the case, we will not bother with having getters and setters... instead, we will allow code to interact with the fields directly.
